    <etym xml:lang="ru">Закономерно из *%itigra%i- (%it%i перед %ii%i → %iс%i, как в <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_yssæʒ"/> и др.). Ср. <mentioned xml:lang="mnj"><lang/><w>tərǧa</w><note
                type="comment" xml:lang="ru"><bibl><ref target="#ref_Зарубин._Мундж."
                        /><biblScope>171</biblScope></bibl></note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en"
                        ><bibl><ref target="#ref_Зарубин._Мундж."
                /><biblScope>171</biblScope></bibl></note></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ydg"
                ><lang/><w>tīrǧ</w><gloss><q>острый</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Morgenstierne._IIFL"/><biblScope>II 256</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned
            xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>tīr</w><gloss><q>стрела</q></gloss></mentioned> (ср. <mentioned
            xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>tez</w><gloss><q>острый</q></gloss></mentioned>), <mentioned
            xml:lang="kho"><lang/><w>ttīra-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"
                ><lang/><w>*tirǧ-(trγ-)</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"
                ><lang/><w>tiγra-</w><gloss><q>острый</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="ae"><w>tiγri-</w><gloss><q>стрела</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned
            xml:lang="peo"><lang/><w>tigra-</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (<mentioned
                    xml:lang="peo"><lang/><w>tigraxauda-</w><gloss><q>с острыми
                    шапками</q></gloss></mentioned> = <mentioned xml:lang="os"
                    ><lang/><w>cīrǧxod</w></mentioned>)</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">
                    (<mentioned xml:lang="peo"><lang/><w>tigraxauda-</w><gloss><q>with sharp
                            caps</q></gloss></mentioned> = <mentioned xml:lang="os"
                        ><lang/><w>cīrǧxod</w></mentioned>)</note><gloss><q>острый</q></gloss></mentioned>.
        — Слово %itigra%i представляет производное от корня %itig%i- ‘острый’, наличного в
        осетинском <ref type="xr" target="#entry_tīǧ"/> | %iteǧ%i ‘острие’, ‘выступающий угол’ и пр.
        q. v. С другим формантом этот корень в <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                    ><lang/><w>tigma-</w><gloss><q>острый</q></gloss></mentioned>.%n<bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II 55, 79</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>25, 28</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref
                target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>21</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
    <etym xml:lang="en">It has regularly developed from *%itigra%i- (%it%i before %ii%i → %iс%i,
        like in <ref type="xr" target="#entry_yssæʒ"/> etc.). Cf. <mentioned xml:lang="mnj"
                ><lang/><w>tərǧa</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"><bibl><ref
                        target="#ref_Зарубин._Мундж."/><biblScope>171</biblScope></bibl></note><note
                type="comment" xml:lang="en"><bibl><ref target="#ref_Зарубин._Мундж."
                        /><biblScope>171</biblScope></bibl></note></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="ydg"><lang/><w>tīrǧ</w><gloss><q>sharp</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Morgenstierne._IIFL"/><biblScope>II 256</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned
            xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>tīr</w><gloss><q>arrow</q></gloss></mentioned> (cf. <mentioned
            xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>tez</w><gloss><q>sharp</q></gloss></mentioned>), <mentioned
            xml:lang="kho"><lang/><w>ttīra-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"
                ><lang/><w>*tirǧ-(trγ-)</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"
                ><lang/><w>tiγra-</w><gloss><q>sharp</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ae"
                ><w>tiγri-</w><gloss><q>arrow</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="peo"
                ><lang/><w>tigra-</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (<mentioned xml:lang="peo"
                        ><lang/><w>tigraxauda-</w><gloss><q>с острыми
                    шапками</q></gloss></mentioned> = <mentioned xml:lang="os"
                    ><lang/><w>cīrǧxod</w></mentioned>)</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">
                    (<mentioned xml:lang="peo"><lang/><w>tigraxauda-</w><gloss><q>with sharp
                            caps</q></gloss></mentioned> = <mentioned xml:lang="os"
                        ><lang/><w>cīrǧxod</w></mentioned>)</note><gloss><q>sharp</q></gloss></mentioned>.
        — The word %itigra%i is a derivative from the root %itig%i- ‘sharp’ which is found in
        Ossetic <ref type="xr" target="#entry_tīǧ"/> | %iteǧ%i ‘cutting edge’, ‘salient angle’ etc.
        q. v. There is the same root with another formant in <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                ><lang/><w>tigma-</w><gloss><q>sharp</q></gloss></mentioned>.%n<bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II 55, 79</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>25, 28</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref
                target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>21</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
</entry>
